---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Flip the Script · Quest Labs">

<div class="edu-page">

  <!-- HERO -->
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero">
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">Quest Labs · Educators Cohort · Fall 2026</div>
      <h1>Flip the<br><em>Script</em></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">A community of praxis for educators trying to fit hope and future transformation into systems built for the past.</p>
      <div class="hero-stats">
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat-num">20</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Educators max</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat-num">12</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Weeks of practice</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat-num">7</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Futures literacies</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat-num">∞</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Possible futures</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-group">
        <a href="#spring-sandbox" class="btn btn-primary">Join Spring Sandbox</a>
        <a href="#signup" class="btn btn-ghost">Fall 2026 Cohort</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-tag">The situation</div>
      <h2>The script we're all<br>still <em>reading from</em></h2>
      <p>The world we're being asked to prepare students for keeps arriving faster than our nervous systems, and the systems built to support us, were ever designed to handle. Most offerings meet educators right there, in that weight, and add more to carry.</p>
      <p>There IS something different. This is what we reach for.</p>

      <div class="problem-cols">
        <div class="prob-col">
          <h4>The water we're swimming in</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Volun-told to attend another training</li>
            <li>Check the box, move on</li>
            <li>One and done, see you next year</li>
            <li>It's always been done like this</li>
            <li>More to carry, less time to breathe</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="prob-col bright">
          <h4>What we're reaching toward</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>You chose to be here</li>
            <li>Praxis as the primary mode</li>
            <li>A practice that deepens over time</li>
            <li>Futures as something you build a relationship with</li>
            <li>More capacity, more community, more possible</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pull">
        <p>The story stays. The learning leaves.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHO IS THIS FOR -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-tag">Who belongs here</div>
      <h2>The whole adult<br><em>ecosystem</em></h2>
      <p>Classroom teachers. Instructional coaches. Curriculum designers. Principals. Assistant principals. Department heads. District leads. Learning experience designers. If you touch the conditions in which young people learn, this room is for you.</p>
      <p>You are not broken. Neither is the system. It is working exactly as it was designed. You, however, are paying attention. That's why you're here.</p>
      <p>Each cohort is capped at 20 to keep it real. Intimate. Honest. Diverse.</p>

      <div class="who-list">
        <div class="who-row">
          <div class="who-label">The Winded Visionary</div>
          <div class="who-text">You believe in futures thinking. You believe in your students. You're running on fumes from trying to do transformative work inside a system that wasn't built for it. This is a place to put down the performance and pick up a practice.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="who-row">
          <div class="who-label">The Curious Skeptic</div>
          <div class="who-text">You've seen "transformative PD" before. Your caution is earned. Come see what happens when the room is actually built differently. If it doesn't land for you, your feedback is the gift.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="who-row">
          <div class="who-label">The Already-Doing-It</div>
          <div class="who-text">You're already running futures-oriented practice in your classroom or school. You need community, language, and a place to go deeper. There are more of us than you think.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="who-row">
          <div class="who-label">The Systems Thinker</div>
          <div class="who-text">Curriculum director. Instructional coach. School leader navigating more than anyone should have to right now. You sit at the intersection of what is and what could be. This practice is built for people who think in ecosystems.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT HAPPENS -->
  <section id="what-happens">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-tag">The practice</div>
      <h2>What actually<br><em>happens</em></h2>
      <p>Flip the Script runs on a 12-week arc, adapted specifically for educators and educational leaders. Each session is a living laboratory. A place where the moment you are trying to meet becomes the curriculum. Capped at 20 people so the room stays real.</p>

      <div class="session-arc">
        <div class="arc-step">
          <div class="arc-num">01</div>
          <h4>Arrival ritual</h4>
          <p>One word check-in. You land before you learn.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-step">
          <div class="arc-num">02</div>
          <h4>World activation</h4>
          <p>Enter the week's futures frame. Different physics every time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-step">
          <div class="arc-num">03</div>
          <h4>Main quest</h4>
          <p>Sarkar Sandbox, futures methods, and productivity practices woven into community crafting of the conditions to embody new cultures and infrastructures of care.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-step">
          <div class="arc-num">04</div>
          <h4>Me / We / Re-search</h4>
          <p>Something solo. Something shared. Something that carries. The sequence is the practice.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-step">
          <div class="arc-num">05</div>
          <h4>Artifact of the week</h4>
          <p>You leave with something made. A key. A map. A seed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pull">
        <p>Go fast, go alone. Go further, go together. We're all in this together.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="section-tag" style="margin-top:3rem">Moving through uncertainty</div>
      <h3 class="subhead">The Black Menagerie as your lens</h3>
      <p>Five archetypes from the Black Menagerie card game serve as the navigational lens for the cohort. Each creature holds a different relationship with emergence, uncertainty, and what wants to be born. You'll recognize yourself in them. You'll grow into the others.</p>

      <div class="session-arc" style="margin-top:1.25rem">
        <div class="arc-step arc-step--preview">
          <span class="preview-badge">Sneak Peek</span>
          <div class="arc-num">◈</div>
          <h4>Black Swan</h4>
          <p>What change is coming that we haven't named yet?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-step arc-step--preview">
          <span class="preview-badge">Sneak Peek</span>
          <div class="arc-num">◈</div>
          <h4>Black Elephant</h4>
          <p>What do we all know but haven't spoken aloud?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-step arc-step--preview">
          <span class="preview-badge">Sneak Peek</span>
          <div class="arc-num">◈</div>
          <h4>Black Jellyfish</h4>
          <p>What are we feeling in our bodies about what's next?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-step arc-step--preview">
          <span class="preview-badge">Sneak Peek</span>
          <div class="arc-num">◈</div>
          <h4>Black Marsh Turtle</h4>
          <p>What do we need to slow down with? Where is rest calling?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-step arc-step--preview">
          <span class="preview-badge">Sneak Peek</span>
          <div class="arc-num">◈</div>
          <h4>Black Sheep</h4>
          <p>What playful disruption wants to emerge?</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-tag" style="margin-top:3rem">The tools</div>
      <h3 class="subhead">Your toolkit for the practice</h3>
      <p>Some tools travel with everyone across the Quest Labs ecosystem. One is built specifically for the educator context.</p>

      <div class="tools-grid">
        <div class="tool-card">
          <span class="tool-badge all">All</span>
          <h4>Sarkar Sandbox</h4>
          <p>Modified from the Sarkar Game. The core session format: embodied, participatory, futures-generative. This is the room where it happens.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-card">
          <span class="tool-badge all">All</span>
          <h4>Quest Cards</h4>
          <p>Your 2032 Job Description, assembled one card at a time. Clocking into our dreams. Joy of Being. One card a month, building something you'll actually want to carry forward.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-card">
          <span class="tool-badge all">All</span>
          <h4>Black Menagerie</h4>
          <p>A futures literacy card game . Five creatures. Seventy-eight cards. Part game, part oracle, part praxis.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-card">
          <span class="tool-badge all">All</span>
          <h4>FRESH Cards</h4>
          <p>Focus, Relationship, Energy, Stimuli, Habits. Your personal practices suite for sustaining the inner work between sessions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-card">
          <span class="tool-badge all">All</span>
          <h4>Wheel of Life</h4>
          <p>A whole-person diagnostic for seeing where you are across the domains of your life. Where is energy flowing? Where is it stuck?</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE FRAMEWORK -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-tag">The framework</div>
      <h2>Seven literacies.<br>One <em>ecology</em>.</h2>
      <p>Most futures literacy frameworks center cognitive sense-making. The ABCDEFG Framework works across a fuller range. Because educators don't just think about the future. They feel it, embody it, play with it, and generate it alongside their students.</p>

      <div class="abc-grid">
        <div class="abc-item"><span class="abc-letter">A</span><span class="abc-word">Affective</span></div>
        <div class="abc-item"><span class="abc-letter">B</span><span class="abc-word">Behavioral</span></div>
        <div class="abc-item"><span class="abc-letter">C</span><span class="abc-word">Cognitive</span></div>
        <div class="abc-item"><span class="abc-letter">D</span><span class="abc-word">Dialectical</span></div>
        <div class="abc-item"><span class="abc-letter">E</span><span class="abc-word">Experiential</span></div>
        <div class="abc-item"><span class="abc-letter">F</span><span class="abc-word">Fun / Creative</span></div>
        <div class="abc-item"><span class="abc-letter">G</span><span class="abc-word">Generative</span></div>
      </div>

      <p style="margin-top:1.5rem">Emerged from 545 contributions by 170 educators across two healing-centered futures gatherings. Not a curriculum. A living methodology. <a href="/foundations" class="inline-link">Explore the foundations ↗</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- NORMS -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-tag">How we hold it</div>
      <h2>The norms that make<br>the room <em>possible</em></h2>

      <div class="norms">
        <div class="norm">
          <h4>The story stays. The learning leaves.</h4>
          <p>What gets shared in the room is held in the room. What shifts in you travels with you everywhere.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="norm">
          <h4>Me-search before we-search before re-search</h4>
          <p>You are the first site of inquiry. Solo reflection before dyad exchange before collective sense-making. Every session, every time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="norm">
          <h4>Play is rigorous</h4>
          <p>This is not a break from serious work. This is serious work in a different register. The experience is the gift. The play is the point.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="norm">
          <h4>We don't perpetuate legacies of labor here</h4>
          <p>You are not here to produce. You are not here to perform. You are here to practice. The pace is the practice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ECOSYSTEM -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-tag">Where this lives</div>
      <h2>Flip the Script and the<br><em>Quest Labs ecosystem</em></h2>
      <p>Flip the Script is the educators entry point into the Quest Labs ecosystem. It sits alongside FLIP (the general 12-week cohort) and Sandbox Sessions (open monthly gatherings) as one of three ways to go deep.</p>

      <div class="ecosystem-row">
        <div class="eco-card">
          <h4>Sandbox Sessions</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Monthly, open door, donations based</li>
            <li>No commitment required</li>
            <li>Leave with one artifact from the future</li>
            <li>The first door in</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="eco-card">
          <h4>FLIP Cohorts</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>12 weeks, general audience</li>
            <li>By invitation, mixed backgrounds</li>
            <li>Full 2032 Job Description arc</li>
            <li>Cohort 02 now forming</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="eco-card highlight" style="margin-top:10px">
        <h4>Flip the Script · Educators Cohort</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>12 weeks, educator-specific context and language</li>
          <li>Sarkar Sandbox adapted for classroom and staffroom realities</li>
          <li>20 educators maximum, Fall 2026 launch</li>
          <li>ABCDEFG framework as the developmental arc</li>
          <li>Quest Cards as your 2032 Job Description, built session by session</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SPRING SANDBOX -->
  <section id="spring-sandbox">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-tag">Sneak peek · May to July 2026</div>
      <h2>Spring Sandbox:<br><em>Breathe into what's coming</em></h2>
      <p>Before the Fall 2026 cohort opens, we're running a free series of virtual sessions for educators who want to taste the practice, shape what it becomes, and end their school year with something other than exhaustion.</p>
      <p>This is co-design as care. You show up. You experience a slice of Flip the Script. You tell us what you need. And if it resonates, you're grandmothered into the Fall founding cohort before the doors open publicly.</p>

      <span id="sponsored"></span>
      <div class="pull">
        <p>20 sponsored seats available for the Fall founding cohort. An invitation for angel investors and educational enthusiasts to pay it forward and materially disrupt systems of oppression and harm.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="tools-grid" style="margin-top:2rem">
        <div class="tool-card">
          <span class="tool-badge edu">Session A · 75 min</span>
          <h4>Sarkar Sandbox 4.0</h4>
          <p>The full immersive format. Futures generative, embodied, participatory. This is the room. Come feel it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-card">
          <span class="tool-badge edu">Session B · 75 min</span>
          <h4>Black Menagerie</h4>
          <p>A taste of the card game at the center of the ecosystem. Five creatures. Futures signals. Collective sense-making.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-card">
          <span class="tool-badge edu">Session C · 60 min</span>
          <h4>Co-Design Conversation</h4>
          <p>What do you actually need as an educator right now? Your answers shape the Fall cohort. This is not a survey. This is a sandbox.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="who-list" style="margin-top:2rem">
        <div class="who-row">
          <div class="who-label">Format</div>
          <div class="who-text">Virtual, via Zoom. Each session stands on its own. Come to one, come to all. Sessions run May through July 2026 as the school year closes and summer opens.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="who-row">
          <div class="who-label">Cost</div>
          <div class="who-text">Donations based. Pay what you can, pay what feels right, pay nothing if now is not the time. Registration is required so we can hold the space with intention. Sponsorships are open for angel investors, educational enthusiasts, foundations, and organizations ready to pay it forward and materially disrupt systems of oppression and harm. 20 sponsored seats available for the Fall founding cohort. This is the investment.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="who-row">
          <div class="who-label">What you get</div>
          <div class="who-text">A real taste of the practice. A voice in what gets built. Feedback that matters. Spring Sandbox participants get first access to the Fall 2026 founding cohort before the doors open publicly. Grandmothered in means your Spring participation counts toward your place.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="who-row">
          <div class="who-label">What we get</div>
          <div class="who-text">Honest feedback from real educators in real end-of-year conditions. That's the research. That's the co-design. We're building this with you, not for you.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="signup-section signup-section--inline">
        <div class="section-tag">Register for Spring Sandbox</div>
        <h3 class="signup-head">Save your spot</h3>
        <p class="signup-lede">Tell us your name, email, and which session(s) you're curious about. We'll send you everything you need.</p>
        <form class="signup-form signup-form--inline" onsubmit="handleSpringSubmit(event)">
          <input type="text" placeholder="Your name" required id="spring-name" />
          <input type="email" placeholder="Your email" required id="spring-email" />
          <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" id="spring-btn">Reserve My Spot →</button>
        </form>
        <div class="session-checks">
          <label><input type="checkbox" id="sess-a" /> Sarkar Sandbox 4.0 (75 min)</label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" id="sess-b" /> Black Menagerie (50 min)</label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" id="sess-c" /> Co-Design Conversation (30 min)</label>
          <label><input type="checkbox" id="sess-all" /> All of the above, obviously</label>
        </div>
        <p class="signup-note" id="spring-msg">Donation based. No one turned away. Sponsorships open.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SIGNUP -->
  <section id="signup">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="signup-section">
        <div class="section-tag" style="text-align:center">Fall 2026 · 20 spots</div>
        <h2>Ready to <em>flip it</em>?</h2>
        <p>Sign-up is an expression of interest, not a commitment. Spots are limited. We'll be in touch with everything you need to decide.</p>
        <form class="signup-form" onsubmit="handleSubmit(event)">
          <input type="text" placeholder="Your name" required id="name-input" />
          <input type="email" placeholder="Your email" required id="email-input" />
          <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" id="submit-btn">Raise My Hand →</button>
        </form>
        <p class="signup-note" id="signup-msg">No spam. Just a heads up when the doors open.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

    <div class="page-bridge" style="max-width:860px; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto; padding-left:2.5rem; padding-right:2.5rem; margin-top:3rem;">
    <p>Not sure where to start?</p>
    <a href="https://lu.ma/questlabs" class="bridge-link">Find a Sandbox Session, open door, no commitment</a>
    <a href="/program" class="bridge-link" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Explore FLIP, the general cohort</a>
    <a href="/about#work-with-us" class="bridge-link" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Bringing this to your school or org? Let's talk</a>
  </div>

<footer>
  <div class="footer-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="footer-logo">Quest Labs</div>
      <div class="footer-tagline">Healing-Centered Futures</div>
    </div>
    <ul class="footer-links">
      <li><a href="/program">FLIP</a></li>
      <li><a href="/educators">Educators</a></li>
      <li><a href="/foundations">Foundations</a></li>
      <li><a href="/black-menagerie">Black Menagerie</a></li>
      <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
      <li><a href="/contact">Contact</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="footer-copy">2026 Quest Labs · Makeda · All futures reserved · Berlin &amp; Beyond</div>
</footer>

</div>

<script is:inline>
  function handleSpringSubmit(e) {
    e.preventDefault();
    const btn = document.getElementById('spring-btn');
    const msg = document.getElementById('spring-msg');
    btn.textContent = '✦ You\'re in';
    btn.disabled = true;
    msg.textContent = 'Spot reserved. Watch your inbox for session details as we get closer.';
    msg.style.color = 'var(--edu-lavender)';
  }

  function handleSubmit(e) {
    e.preventDefault();
    const btn = document.getElementById('submit-btn');
    const msg = document.getElementById('signup-msg');
    btn.textContent = '✦ Received';
    btn.disabled = true;
    msg.textContent = 'You\'re on the list. We\'ll be in touch before Fall 2026.';
    msg.style.color = 'var(--edu-lavender)';
  }
</script>

<style is:global>
  /* =========================================================
     EDUCATORS PAGE — scoped under .edu-page using CSS nesting
     Tokens prefixed with --edu- so they can't collide with
     the site-wide tokens defined in src/styles/global.css
     ROYAL palette: violet + lavender + black space. No gold/teal.
     ========================================================= */

  .edu-page {
    /* Royal token palette — scoped to this page */
    --edu-void: #0a0a0f;
    --edu-void2: #111118;
    --edu-violet: #6B3FA0;
    --edu-violet-mid: #8B5CC8;
    --edu-violet-light: #B48FE0;
    --edu-lavender: #C4A8E8;
    --edu-mist: #E8E4F2;
    --edu-cream: #FDFCFA;
    --edu-text-primary: #FDFCFA;
    --edu-text-muted: #9A90B8;
    --edu-text-dim: #5C5578;
    --edu-border: rgba(107,63,160,0.2);
    --edu-border-soft: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);

    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    color: var(--edu-text-primary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 300;

    /* LAYOUT */
    & .container { max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2.5rem; }
    & .container-wide { max-width: 1080px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2.5rem; }

    /* HERO */
    & .hero {
      padding: 5rem 0 5rem;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    & .hero::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      top: -80px; right: -100px;
      width: 500px; height: 500px;
      background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(107,63,160,0.18) 0%, transparent 65%);
      pointer-events: none;
      z-index: 0;
    }
    & .hero > * { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
    & .hero-eyebrow {
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: 500;
      letter-spacing: 0.2em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--edu-violet-light);
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
    & .hero-eyebrow::before {
      content: '◎';
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--edu-violet-mid);
    }
    & .hero h1 {
      font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
      font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1.1;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      color: var(--edu-cream);
      margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    }
    & .hero h1 em {
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--edu-lavender);
    }
    & .hero-sub {
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.5vw, 1.4rem);
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--edu-text-muted);
      max-width: 560px;
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    & .hero-stats {
      display: flex;
      gap: 2.5rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }
    & .stat-num {
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      font-weight: 400;
      color: var(--edu-lavender);
      line-height: 1;
      display: block;
    }
    & .stat-label {
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: 500;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--edu-text-dim);
    }
    & .cta-group {
      display: flex;
      gap: 1rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    /* BUTTONS */
    & .btn {
      display: inline-block;
